    {
        "content": "<p>Hey folks, sorry for resurrecting this old thread. It seems that in general we are compiling everything (except core) with edition 2021 in RA even though recently vendored crates may use other editions (e.g. quote uses 2018 until <a href=\"https://github.com/dtolnay/quote/commit/bcb39072ab596206331e2da5f67ee4551947b0b4\">1.0.43</a> while our copy is 1.0.40).</p>\n<p>We can fix this by updating quote but in general we're going to run into this again as crates start to update to edition 2024.</p>\n<p>We also have this problem with <code>feature</code> flags for these newly vendored crates: <code>proc_macro2</code>, <code>syn</code>, and <code>quote</code> all have features enabled and none of these are known to RA.</p>",
        "id": 568258052,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1768494211
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think for vendored crated their edition can be hardcoded</p>",
        "id": 568258485,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1768494330
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We need special handling for core as they need to match compiler</p>",
        "id": 568258552,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1768494350
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We need that special handling not just for core, but also for alloc, std, and proc_macro.</p>",
        "id": 568260592,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1768494896
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will send a patch.</p>",
        "id": 568260737,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1768494924
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I sent patches for sysroot and quote editions. Any thoughts on the <code>feature</code> flags?</p>",
        "id": 568263254,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1768495619
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I am wrong! <code>feature</code> is indeed correctly plumbed into RA. Kudos to Miguel for taking care of this.</p>",
        "id": 568265161,
        "sender_full_name": "Tamir Duberstein",
        "timestamp": 1768496121
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We only build core from sysroot. Others are shipped pre-built I think? I think this should just be fixed up in the script</p>",
        "id": 568266084,
